consumer_reviews.review_text: I got the pad Pad Thai And the flavor was great but I do recommend that if you're a wuss like me go for not spicey. I got the mild and my mouth has been on fire for about an hour now but it was delicious￼

consumer_reviews.review_text: Egg shell on Fried Rice  Sticky Rice didn't taste good not enough moisture hard to chew and swallow I will not get that again. Hard a weird plastic aftertaste maybe because they wrap the stick rice in plastic heat up and then foil wrap around it.

Hard a weird plastic aftertaste maybe because they wrap the stick rice in plastic heat up and then foil wrap around it.

consumer_reviews.review_text: My go-tos:: wonton soup (absolutely delicious wontons), Pad Agra Tiem (deliciously spicy) and the Pad Himmaparn (yummy). I don't think you can go wrong with anything you order from here but these are my faves.
consumer_reviews.marked_up_review_text: My go-tos:: <<taggedItemId=24821387>>wonton soup<</taggedItemId>> (absolutely delicious wontons), Pad Agra Tiem (deliciously spicy) and the <<taggedItemId=24820459>>Pad Himmaparn<</taggedItemId>> (yummy). I don't think you can go wrong with anything you order from here but these are my faves.

consumer_reviews.review_text: The curry was good, medium was a bit more spicy than I anticipated. But the flavors were great. I expected the fresh rolls to be more like salad rolls, but they weren't. That is more my mistake than the restaurant.
Another Thai place that can't do panang curry. Watery, so they used coconut milk instead of the more-expensive cream, no kaffir lime and it tasted like chicken instead of beef.  And it wasn't cheap
